class Solution {
    public int searchInsert(int[] nums, int target) {
        // ✅ Initialize search boundaries
        int l = 0;                     // Left pointer (start of array)
        int r = nums.length - 1;       // Right pointer (end of array)

        // ✅ Standard binary search loop
        while (l <= r) {
            // Midpoint calculation (avoids overflow compared to (l+r)/2)
            int m = l + (r - l) / 2;

            // If target is found at mid, return its index
            if (nums[m] == target) {
                return m;
            }

            // If target is smaller than nums[m],
            // it must be in the left half → move right pointer left
            if (nums[m] > target) {
                r = m - 1;
            } else {
                // Otherwise, target is greater → move left pointer right
                l = m + 1;
            }
        }

        // ✅ If target is not found:
        // 'l' will be the correct insertion position
        // because it points to the first element greater than target
        return l;
    }
}


\\ Time Complexity: 
   𝑂(log𝑛) → binary search.

\\ Space Complexity: 
   𝑂(1)

\\ Returns either the index of target if found, or the insertion position to keep the array sorted.
